<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="biology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
Host fungus is 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Meruliaceae" genus="Bjerkandera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bjerkandera adusta" order="Polyporales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="adusta">Bjerkandera adusta</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Chandler, PJ" journalOrPublisher="Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica Volume 36, Brill, Leiden, Boston, Koeln" pageId="17" pageNumber="112" title="The flat-footed flies (Diptera: Opetiidae and Platypezidae) of Europe." year="2001">Chandler 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The females can be observed during oviposition on sporocarps of the host 
<taxonomicName genus="Platypezoidea" kingdom="fungi" lsidName="Platypezoidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" rank="kingdom">fungi</taxonomicName>
on tree stumps (Figure 3). It is a species with autumnal activity; adult flight period is in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="IX–XI">IX-XI</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
